            <span class="eyebrow">What your fee buys</span>
            <h2>Your protection day, step by step.</h2>
            <p class="lede">Not a product or a subscription — a full day of expert work, done in person and in your presence. This is what happens, in order.</p>
        </div>
        <ol class="process">
            <li><span class="n">01</span><div><h3>Threat model</h3><p>We map every device, account, and channel you rely on — and exactly who can reach each one.</p></div></li>
            <li><span class="n">02</span><div><h3>Indicators-of-compromise scan</h3><p>We check your devices and accounts for what may already be wrong: rogue sessions, unfamiliar logins, stalkerware, silent forwarding rules.</p></div></li>
            <li><span class="n">03</span><div><h3>Authentication hardening</h3><p>We end live sessions, rotate what's exposed, and set passkeys and your hardware key as the locks — so a password someone already knows is no longer enough.</p></div></li>
            <li><span class="n">04</span><div><h3>Operating-system hardening</h3><p>Encryption, lockdown settings, and OS configuration brought to the NSA, NIST, and NCSC baselines used by government agencies.</p></div></li>
            <li><span class="n">05</span><div><h3>App &amp; cloud configuration</h3><p>Permissions, location sharing, family plans, shared albums, and backups reviewed one by one — and closed.</p></div></li>
            <li><span class="n">06</span><div><h3>Network, vehicle &amp; connected devices<span class="opt">add-ons &amp; higher tiers</span></h3><p>Router, smart-home, and vehicle accounts brought back under your sole control.</p></div></li>
            <li><span class="n">07</span><div><h3>Coaching</h3><p>We train you on the habits, the hardware key, and the secure channel — so the protection holds long after the day ends.</p></div></li>
            <li><span class="n">08</span><div><h3>Certificate of Hardening</h3><p>A signed record of every measure applied, dated for your attorney and your legal file.</p></div></li>
        </ol>
    </div>
</section>

